history.text: Hello.
Hey there, how are you?
I'm doing great myself you?
Haha, same same. So lets talk about Maleficent, what are your thoughts?
Good to know. The movie to me is very interesting, it just tackles the whole fairy tale story telling in a different method.
I can't disagree on that, I really feel like this movie separates itself from the common fairy tales.
Yeah, very true, it may be a weakness for other people but to me, it makes me feel like this movie is significantly different and separates itself from the others.
Right. Although different, I will say that Angelina Jolie played the part of Maleficent really well.
Definitely so, I just feel like she is the one that really carries the whole movie to be a good one.
I will agree on that, she is also so graceful yet menacing for the part which is perfect.
I guess the make up also helped because she looked very you know, villianish. haha.
Lol yeah, but I think it looked great but youre right.
Right, I feel like the whole narrative to the movie is a bit decent but the execution felt flat to me, it became generic.
Hmm. You think so?
I just feel like all the actors were great but they could have done a better job portraying significant scenes.
Ohh yeah, I am having a bit of trouble remembering any scenes actually, but that is right, actors were great.
Lol, I remember this movie being dark, theme wise, most of the parts that I can remember are so dark like it happened in the night.
Gloomy right, I think they did that on purpose to set the mood for the feelings for Maleficent.
Hmm, I agree.
I can't believe the low rating for the movie still, it should deserve at least 70 percent right?
Maybe a 6/10, like I said, I enjoyed the movie, but some scenes are not that popping out or significant that it falls flat.
Yeah, the actor who plays Stefan is a good actor by the way.
Right?
I remember him being in other movies.
Other few good movies right.
The biggest takeaway from this movie is how Angelina Jolie really tends to carry subpar movies to be watchable, lol.
Very correct, she is such a great actress.
And if I can remember she feels like she is really a very flexible actress for that matter.
Haha, true, she is one of a kind.
Her and the actor who played Stefan, Shartlo Copley.
Haha, yes.
Thank you for your time, you have a good day!
Thank you, same to you.
